To create a footnote for the authors list in LaTeX, you can use the `footmisc` package. Here's a step-by-step guide:

1. Include the `footmisc` package in your LaTeX document's preamble:

```latex
\usepackage[footnotesize,colorinlist,singleline]{footmisc}
```

2. Define a command for the footnote mark in the authors list:

```latex
\renewcommand{\thefootnote}{\fnsymbol{footnote}}
```

3. Add footnotes to the authors list:

```latex
\author{Author Name\textsuperscript{\ref{footnote1}} \And Author Name\textsuperscript{\ref{footnote2}}}

\title{Your Title}

\maketitle

\footnotetext[1]{Footnote text for the first author}
\footnotetext[2]{Footnote text for the second author}
```

Replace "Author Name" with the actual author names, "Your Title" with the title of your document, and "Footnote text" with the text you want to appear in the footnote.

4. Compile your LaTeX document to generate the footnotes in the authors list.
